1 AN ACT making appropriations for the operations, maintenance, and support of the
2 Legislative Branch of the Commonwealth of Kentucky.
3 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
4 Section 1. The Legislative Branch Budget is as follows:
5 PART I
6 OPERATING BUDGET
7 Funds Appropriations: Funds are appropriated to the Legislative Research
8 Commission for the Legislative Branch of government out of the General Fund and
9 Restricted Funds accounts for the fiscal year beginning July 1, 2026, and ending June 30,
10 2027, and for the fiscal year beginning July 1, 2027, and ending June 30, 2028, in the
11 following discrete sums, or so much thereof as may be necessary. Each appropriation is
12 made by the source of respective fund or funds accounts to be used for the purposes of
13 the Legislative Branch of government of the Commonwealth of Kentucky.
14 A. LEGISLATIVE BRANCH
15 Budget Units
16 2026-27 2027-28
17 1. General Assembly
18 General Fund 23,908,000 25,920,200
19 Restricted Funds 75,000 175,000
20 TOTAL 23,983,000 26,095,200
21 (1) Kentucky Legislative Ethics Commission: Included in the above General
22 Fund appropriation is $567,700 in each fiscal year of the 2026-2028 fiscal biennium for
23 the Kentucky Legislative Ethics Commission. Included in the above Restricted Funds
24 appropriation is $75,000 in fiscal year 2026-2027 and $175,000 in fiscal year 2027-2028
25 for the Kentucky Legislative Ethics Commission.
26 (2) Kentucky Long-Term Policy Research Center: Notwithstanding KRS
27 7B.010 to 7B.090, operation of the Kentucky Long-Term Policy Research Center and its
