5 (3) Pension Benefit Increase: Notwithstanding KRS 6.521(3), no pension
6 benefit increase shall be granted to recipients of a retirement allowance under KRS 6.500
7 to 6.577 on July 1, 2026.
8 (4) Legislators Compensation: Notwithstanding KRS 6.190 and 6.213, the daily
9 compensation provided by KRS 6.190 and the interim expense allowance provided by
10 KRS 6.213 for members of the General Assembly shall be as authorized by the 2024-
11 2026 biennium and shall continue as adjusted on January 1, 2027, by the salary increment
12 provided to state employees in the State/Executive Branch Budget.
13 2026-27 2027-28
14 2. Legislative Research Commission
15 General Fund 66,218,400 66,804,500
16 (1) Legislative Record: Notwithstanding KRS 7.105, distribution of the final
17 issue of the Legislative Record and the interim Legislative Record shall be suspended
18 effective July 1, 2026.
19 (2) Legislative Publications: Notwithstanding KRS Chapters 27A and 57, the
20 Acts of the General Assembly, the Journals of the Senate and House of Representatives,
21 and the official Kentucky statute publications may be distributed by use of electronic
22 versions only, at the discretion of the Director of the Legislative Research Commission.
23 (3) Judicial Branch Salary Compensation Study: Included in the above
24 General Fund appropriation is $1,000,000 in fiscal year 2026-2027 to support a contract
25 with an external consultant to conduct a comprehensive salary and compensation study
26 for the elected and nonelected personnel of the Judicial Branch. The study shall review
27 current classifications, compensation levels, and market competitiveness and shall
Page 2 of 7
HB050390.100 - 1377 - XXXX 4/14/2026 4:20 PM Vetoed in Part and Overridden

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 503/VO
1 include recommendations for potential adjustments to ensure equitable and competitive
2 compensation practices. The consultant shall submit the results of the study to the Interim
3 Joint Committee on Appropriations and Revenue by July 1, 2027.
4 (4) Operating Expense Reduction: The Director of the Legislative Research
5 Commission shall, by October 1, 2026, submit a report to the Legislative Oversight and
6 Investigations Committee and the Interim Joint Committee on Appropriations and
7 Revenue regarding the historical and projected operational expenditures for the
8 Legislative Research Commission. The report shall include:
9 (a) A summary of actual and projected operational expenditures for fiscal years
10 2025-2026, 2026-2027, and 2027-2028;
11 (b) A description of the administrative steps and prior approval processes
12 implemented by the Director to reduce annual operational expenses; and
13 (c) The total projected savings for the 2026-2028 fiscal biennium resulting from
14 these cost-reduction efforts.
