1 spirits by the drink to attendees of state, regional, or national conference.
2 (7) Nothing in this section shall prohibit the employees of retail drink licensees,
3 including but not limited to NQ1, NQ2, NQ3, and licensed caterers from serving or
4 selling wine, malt beverages, and distilled spirits by the drink at a state, regional, or
5 national conference on the account of or on behalf of a nonprofit organization or the
6 organizer or sponsor of a state, regional, or national conference that holds a special
7 temporary nonprofit license.
8 PART III
9 BUDGET REDUCTION OR SURPLUS EXPENDITURE PLAN
10 The Legislative Branch shall participate in any Budget Reduction Plan or Surplus
11 Expenditure Plan in accordance with KRS Chapter 48, except that obligations essential to
12 the constitutional duties of the Legislative Branch shall be exempt from any Budget
13 Reduction Plan. The level of participation in a Budget Reduction Plan shall be at the
14 discretion of the Director and shall not exceed the actual percentage of revenue shortfall.
